IRS990.ActivityOrMissionDesc: COMMUNITY HEALTH CARE PROVIDES PRIMARY MEDICAL, DENTAL, AND BEHAVIORAL HEALTH CARE TO INDIVIDUALS IN THE COMMUNITIES THEY SERVE.
IRS990.MissionDesc: COMMUNITY HEALTH CARE PROVIDES THE COMMUNITIES WE SERVE WITH EXCELLENCE IN PATIENT-CENTERED MEDICAL, DENTAL, AND BEHAVIORAL HEALTH CARE THAT IS COMPASSIONATE, AFFORDABLE, AND ACCESSIBLE.
IRS990.Desc: COMMUNITY HEALTH CARE, INC., PROVIDES PRIMARY MEDICAL CARE IN EIGHT LOCATIONS IN BOTH IOWA AND ILLINOIS. MEDICAL SERVICES INCLUDE INTERNAL MEDICINE, FAMILY PRACTICE, PEDIATRICS, LABORATORY, PHARMACY, AND OB/GYN. MEDICAL PATIENTS SERVED DURING FISCAL YEAR 2023 WERE 25,115 IN 98,942 MEDICAL VISITS. THOSE WHO QUALIFY ARE OFFERED A SLIDING FEE SCALE.

ProgSrvcAccomActy2Grp.Desc: COMMUNITY HEALTH CARE, INC. PROVIDES DENTAL CARE IN THREE LOCATIONS IN BOTH IOWA AND ILLINOIS. DENTAL PATIENTS SERVED WERE 14,397 IN 30,045 DENTAL VISITS. ALL PEOPLE IN NEED ARE SERVED. THOSE WHO QUALIFY ARE OFFERED A SLIDING FEE SCALE.

ProgSrvcAccomActy3Grp.Desc: COMMUNITY HEALTH CARE, INC. PROVIDES BEHAVIORAL HEALTH CARE IN FIVE LOCATIONS IN BOTH IOWA AND ILLINOIS. BEHAVIORAL HEALTH PATIENTS SERVED WERE 3,059 IN 12,993 VISITS. ALL PEOPLE IN NEED ARE SERVED. THOSE WHO QUALIFY ARE OFFERED A SLIDING FEE SCALE.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: SCHEDULE C, PART II-B, LINES 1(A), 1(B), AND 1(G)
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: LOBBYING ACTIVITIES: THE ORGANIZATION WILL FROM TIME TO TIME ASK ITS BOARD MEMBERS, LEADERSHIP TEAM, AND EMPLOYEES TO CONTACT THEIR LOCAL LEGISLATORS IF THERE IS PENDING LEGISLATION THAT COULD HELP OR HARM THE HEALTH CENTER. THE SUM TOTAL OF THE TIME AND EFFORTS THE HEALTH CENTER SPENDS ON DIRECT LOBBYING EFFORTS IS NOT MATERIAL TO THE OVERALL EXPENSES OF THE ORGANIZATION.

OTHER LOBBYING ACTIVITIES: THE ORGANIZATION PAYS DUES TO THE ILLINOIS PRIMARY CARE ASSOCIATION AND THE IOWA PRIMARY CARE ASSOCIATION. A PORTION OF THESE DUES MAY BE ATTRIBUTABLE TO LOBBYING EXPENSES. HOWEVER, A REVIEW OF THESE ORGANIZATIONS' FORM 990 RETURNS REVEAL NO POLITICAL ACTIVITY HAS OCCURRED WITH THE USE OF THESE DUES.

ENDOWMENT FUNDS: A FUND WAS SET UP TO HONOR DR. MARY MARIANI, DDS WHO BELIEVED EVERYONE DESERVES A BEAUTIFUL SMILE. THE FUNDS ARE TO BENEFIT THE CHC DENTAL CLINICS WHERE MARY SERVED FOR OVER 25 YEARS. A FUND WAS ESTABLISHED DECEMBER 23, 1999 BY MATERNAL HEALTH CENTER, INC. WITH THE MERGER OF MATERNAL HEALTH AND COMMUNITY HEALTH CARE, INC. APRIL 1, 2016 THE ENDOWMENT WAS RE DESIGNATED TO CHC TO BE USED FOR WOMEN'S HEALTH.

UNCERTAIN TAX POSITIONS: MANAGEMENT HAS EVALUATED THEIR INCOME TAX POSITIONS UNDER THE GUIDANCE INCLUDED IS ASC 740. BASED ON THEIR REVIEW, MANAGEMENT HAS NOT IDENTIFIED ANY MATERIAL UNCERTAIN TAX POSITIONS TO BE RECORDED OR DISCLOSED IN THE FINANCIAL STATEMENTS.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, SCHEDULE I, PART I, LINE 2
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: PROCEDURES FOR MONITORING THE USE OF GRANT FUNDS: COMMUNITY HEALTH CARE INC. MONITORS THE GRANT EXPENDITURES BY REQUIRING THE SUBRECIPIENT OF ANY GRANT TO PROVIDE A BUDGET OF ITS EXPENDITURES, PROOF OF LIABILITY, YEAR END AUDITIED FINANCIAL STATEMENTS AND PERFORMS A DESK REVIEW AUDIT ANNUALLY.

BONUSES CONTINGENT ON NET EARNINGS: THE ORGANIZATION HAS ESTABLISHED AN INCENTIVE PLAN THAT IS DEPENDENT UPON THE ORGANIZATION MEETING CERTAIN NET EARNINGS TARGETS. AFTER THE ORGANIZATION MEETS THESE TARGETS, THE PLAN ALLOWS FOR STAFF TO EARN A BONUS BASED ON A PERCENTAGE OF THEIR ANNUAL COMPENSATION IF THE STAFF MEETS TARGETS BASED ON THEIR INDIVIDUAL PERFORMANCE, PATIENT EXPERIENCE TARGETS AND STAFF ENGAGEMENT TARGETS.

NON-FIXED PAYMENTS: THE BONUS IS FACTORED ON SEVERAL ITEMS. THE MAIN PORTION OF THE BONUS IS GENERATED BY PATIENT VOLUME. EACH PROVIDER HAS A MINIMUM NUMBER OF FACE TO FACE BILLABLE ENCOUNTERS THAT THEY NEED TO SEE ON A YEARLY BASIS. THE MINIMUM NUMBER IS ADJUSTED ACCORDING TO SPECIALTY AND CLINIC TYPE, I.E. DENTISTS VS. INTERNIST. ONCE THE PROVIDER HAS MET THE MINIMUM NUMBER OF FACE TO FACE BILLABLE ENCOUNTERS, THEY BEGIN TO ACCRUE A BONUS FOR EACH PATIENT THEY SEE. THERE ARE ALSO QUALITY INDICATORS THAT ARE TRACKED FOR EACH PROVIDER WHICH CAN EARN THEM SMALL BONUSES. EXAMPLES WOULD BE: TIMELY DICTATION, PATIENT SATISFACTION, A1C LEVELS UNDER CONTROL FOR DIABETICS, PROPER IMMUNIZATIONS GIVEN FOR CHILDREN, ETC. THESE QUALITY INDICATORS ARE ALSO SPECIFIC TO THE PROVIDER TYPE.
NUMBER OF CONTRIBUTORS: THE NUMBER ENTERED IN COLUMN B REPRESENTS THE NUMBER OF CONTRIBUTIONS RECEIVED DURING THE YEAR.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 11B
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: REVIEW PROCESS OF 990: THE FORM 990 IS PREPARED BY AN INDEPENDENT ACCOUNTING FIRM BASED ON THE AUDITED FINANCIALS STATEMENTS AND INFORMATION PROVIDED BY THE ACCOUNTING DEPARTMENT OF COMMUNITY HEALTH CARE INC. THE CHIEF FINANCIAL OFFICER OF THE ORGANIZATION FIRST REVIEWS THE RETURN SEPARATELY IN DETAIL. AFTER THIS REVIEW, THE AUDIT COMMITTEE REVIEWS THE FORM 990 AND RECOMMENDS FILING TO THE BOARD OF DIRECTORS. THE BOARD OF DIRECTORS IS THEN PROVIDED A COPY OF THE RETURN AND AUTHORIZES FILING. THE BOARD IS ALLOWED TO ASK QUESTIONS AND MAKE COMMENTS REGARDING THE RETURN.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 12C
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: CONFLICT OF INTEREST POLICY COMPLIANCE: ALL CONFLICTS ARE MONITORED THROUGHOUT THE YEAR. IF A POTENTIAL CONFLICT ARISES, THE BOARD WOULD BE NOTIFIED AND STEPS ARE TAKEN TO REMEDY THE CONFLICT. IF A QUESTION CONCERNING A CONFLICT OF INTEREST FOR ANY DIRECTOR IS RAISED, AND IN THE ABSENCE OF THE DIRECTOR RECUSING HIM OR HERSELF, A WRITTEN SECRET BALLOT MAY BE USED BY THE REMAINING DIRECTORS TO DETERMINE IF SUCH CONFLICT OF INTEREST EXISTS. SHOULD A CONFLICT OF INTEREST, PECUNIARY OR OTHERWISE, BE DETERMINED FOR ANY DIRECTOR, SUCH DIRECTOR SHALL BE EXCLUDED FROM VOTING ON THAT SUBJECT MATTER. A SIMPLE AFFIRMATIVE MAJORITY OF THOSE PRESENT SHALL RULE. IN ALL EVENTS, A DIRECTOR SHALL DISCLOSE ANY POSSIBLE CONFLICTS OF INTEREST.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 15A
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: COMPENSATION DETERMINATION POLICY: THE CEO IS A CONTRACTED EMPLOYEE. THE BOARD OF DIRECTORS COMPLETES A PERFORMANCE REVIEW IN WRITING ON AN ANNUAL BASIS BASED ON COMPENSATION SURVEYS CONDUCTED ANNUALLY BY THE PRIMARY CARE ASSOCIATIONS IN IOWA AND ILLINOIS AND THE NATIONAL ASSOCIATION OF COMMUNITY HEALTH CENTERS. AT THAT TIME, THEY MAY AWARD A DISCRETIONARY BONUS OR MERIT INCREASE BASED UPON CEO AND ORGANIZATIONAL PERFORMANCE. CHANGES TO SALARY ARE NOTED IN THE CONTRACT. THE ORIGINAL, CURRENT CONTRACT IS HOUSED WITH HUMAN RESOURCES AND A COPY GOES TO PAYROLL. THE LAST COMPENSATION REVIEW WAS PERFORMED IN 2023.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 15B
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: COMPENSATION DETERMINATION POLICY: OTHER OFFICER AND KEY EMPLOYEE COMPENSATION DETERMINATION POLICY: COMPENSATION FOR KEY EMPLOYEE IS SET BY THE CEO AND DIRECTOR OF HUMAN RESOURCES BASED ON COMPENSATION SURVEYS CONDUCTED ANNUALLY BY THE PRIMARY CARE ASSOCIATION IN IOWA AND ILLINOIS AND THE NATIONAL ASSOCIATION OF COMMUNITY HEALTH CENTERS. THE LAST COMPENSATION REVIEW WAS PERFORMED IN 2023.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION C, LINE 19
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: DOCUMENT DISCLOSURE POLICY: THE ORGANIZATION'S FINANCIAL STATEMENTS, IRS FORM 990, AND OTHER DOCUMENTS AND POLICIES ARE MADE AVAILABLE TO INTERESTED PARTIES, UPON REQUEST, FOR VIEWING ON-SITE.
